post_text: For your information:
shared_text:
CCS District 135
September 4 at 5:59 PM ·

Centralia City School District 135 will remain on our normal schedule and continue with in person learning as usual. We are coordinating with the local health departments on a daily basis to ensure that in person learning can continue safely, and have not been advised to place our district under any further restrictions at this time. The temporary pause in student attendance at Centralia High School will not affect any students attending Centralia City Schools unless they are notified by the Health Department on an individual basis. The Marion County Health Department has informed us that the positive cases that have been identified at the high school do not have a direct connection to our students or staff members. We will continue to follow guidance from IDPH, the CDC, and our local health departments and we thank you for your continued support.
text:
For your information:

CCS District 135
September 4 at 5:59 PM ·

Centralia City School District 135 will remain on our normal schedule and continue with in person learning as usual. We are coordinating with the local health departments on a daily basis to ensure that in person learning can continue safely, and have not been advised to place our district under any further restrictions at this time. The temporary pause in student attendance at Centralia High School will not affect any students attending Centralia City Schools unless they are notified by the Health Department on an individual basis. The Marion County Health Department has informed us that the positive cases that have been identified at the high school do not have a direct connection to our students or staff members. We will continue to follow guidance from IDPH, the CDC, and our local health departments and we thank you for your continued support.

CCS District 135
July 23 at 3:00 PM ·

We know right now all our families are carefully weighing the pros and cons between our in-person and remote learning options for the 2020-2021 school year. Even if you haven't decided which option you feel would be best for your student, we strongly encourage you to register online if possible. You are not asked to pick a learning option when you register. We will have a way for you to pick that designation at a later date. Not only is registering online simple, but it will save you from having to stand in lines on registration day!

Need help or your login information? Call 618-532-1907, ext 1120 and someone will be able to assist you.
#savetimeregisteronline
#registerincomfortathome

The Centralia Halloween Parade Theme Contest is open to all students in the Centralia City Schools district. Students can submit their THEME IDEA, along with their NAME, AGE, GRADE, and SCHOOL.

Email your entry to: contest@centraliahalloweenparade.com or mail it to: Halloween Parade, PO Box 410, Centralia, IL 62801

Entries must be emailed or postmarked by midnight, May 23rd, 2020!

The winner will ride in the parade as a VIP and win a pizza party for his or her class. The party will be held when school resumes in the fall.

post_text:
Happy Teacher Appreciation Week, Mrs. Laurie Miller!

Dear Mrs. Laurie Miller,

I appreciate you today and every day! I love how you give your own time to help students even when it is your planning time. You make the classroom comfortable and you have a caring heart. I have had such a great year with you and can’t believe I won’t get to come back to Jordan next year as a student. Thank you for helping me learn and become smarter! Be sure to treat yourself to some ice cream even though you would rather have something healthier! 😂

Love,
Aubrey Moore

post_text:
Happy Teacher Appreciation Week, Mrs. Stroud!

Isabella started Jordan Elementary in the beginning of September from another school. All the staff welcomed us with open arms. Isabella has Mrs. Stroud for her first year at Jordan school and she transitioned without any problems and loved to go to school! We could not of asked for a better experience this year at Jordan School and feel blessed with Isabella having Mrs. Stroud as her Teacher. She truly cares and loves for her students.

Thanks!
